          "number": 2,
          "slidetitle": "Risks of AI API Connections",
          "subtitle": "What can go wrong and why",
          "slidecontent": "• Exposed API keys granting unauthorised access to your AI service account\n• Data leakage when sensitive user inputs are sent to third-party servers\n• Prompt injection attacks manipulating AI responses\n• Overly broad permissions allowing attackers to abuse connected systems\n• No visibility into how external providers store or process your data\n• Unexpected costs from unthrottled or hijacked API usage",
          "do_not_include": false
        },
        {
          "number": 3,
          "slidetitle": "Risks of Insecure AI APIs",
          "subtitle": "What can go wrong, and why.",
          "slidecontent": "• Exposed API keys granting attackers full access to your AI service account\n• Data leakage through poorly secured request and response payloads\n• Excessive costs from unauthorised or runaway API usage\n• Prompt injection attacks manipulating AI behaviour in unexpected ways\n• No audit trail when logging and monitoring are overlooked\n• Compliance violations if sensitive user data crosses unsecured API boundaries",
