        },
        {
          "number": 6,
          "slidetitle": "Securing Your API Connections",
          "subtitle": "Best practices for safe integration",
          "slidecontent": "• Always use HTTPS\n• Rotate API keys regularly\n• Restrict key permissions tightly\n• Validate all API responses\n• Log and monitor API calls",
          "do_not_include": false
        },
        {
          "number": 7,
          "slidetitle": "Mitigating AI API Risks",
          "subtitle": "Practical Steps to Reduce Exposure",
          "slidecontent": "• Validate all API responses\n• Rotate keys regularly\n• Log every API call\n• Limit API permissions strictly\n• Use HTTPS always",
          "do_not_include": true
        },
        {
          "number": 8,
          "slidetitle": "Key Points to Remember",
          "subtitle": "Core principles for secure AI integration",
          "slidecontent": "• Always validate and sanitise data flowing between your application and any external AI service\n• Never expose raw API keys in client-side code or public repositories\n• Treat AI outputs as untrusted input\n• Apply the principle of least privilege when configuring API access and permissions\n• Log and monitor API calls to detect unusual patterns or unexpected behaviour early\n• Start small, review your integration against an established security checklist before moving to production",
          "do_not_include": false
